1.text: Cover the end of a mop with a plastic bag.
1.vid: /6/65/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 1 Version 3.360p.mp4

2.text: Plunge your toilet with the mop.
2.vid: /0/04/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 2 Version 4.360p.mp4

3.text: Keep plunging with the mop until your toilet is unclogged.
3.vid: /0/00/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 3 Version 3.360p.mp4

4.text: Bend a metal coat hanger into a curve.
4.vid: /8/81/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 4 Version 3.360p.mp4

5.text: Push the wire up into the toilet canal and try to clear the way.
5.vid: /8/89/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 5 Version 3.360p.mp4

6.text: Keep pushing the wire into the toilet canal until it's unclogged.
6.vid: /4/41/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 6 Version 4.360p.mp4

7.text: Cover the end of a toilet brush with a plastic bag.
7.vid: /5/55/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 7 Version 3.360p.mp4

8.text: Use the end of the toilet brush to plunge your toilet.
8.vid: /b/b6/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 8 Version 3.360p.mp4

9.text: Continue plunging until your toilet is unclogged.
9.vid: /d/dc/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 9 Version 3.360p.mp4

10.text: Mix 1 part baking soda and 1 part vinegar in a large container.

11.text: Pour the baking soda and vinegar mixture into your clogged toilet.
11.vid: /f/f8/Unblock a Toilet when You Have No Plunger Step 11 Version 3.360p.mp4

12.text: Let the mixture sit for 5-10 minutes and then flush your toilet.
